com.camerontec.util.concurrent.circularbuffer

Class LockingCircularBufferProducer<S,T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.util.concurrent.circularbuffer.LockingCircularBufferProducer<S,T>
  • Type Parameters:
    S - The source type.
    T - The target type.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    CircularBufferProducer<S,T>

    public final class LockingCircularBufferProducer<S,T>
extends Object
implements CircularBufferProducer<S,T>
    A locking CircularBufferProducer implementation.

    This implementation forces concurrently producing threads to be serialized via a lock. This can be more efficient than the circular buffers underlying algorithm for commit ordering, especially when the number of concurrently producing threads is large.
